<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
The subfamily and tribal position of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Holcophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holcophora" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holcophora</taxonomicName>
is still somewhat uncertain. Meyrick placed 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Holcophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holcophora" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holcophora</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Aponoea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aponoea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aponoea</taxonomicName>
, separated only by 
<taxonomicName authority="Staudinger, 1871" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Rhynchopacha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhynchopacha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rhynchopacha</taxonomicName>
Staudinger, 1871 (= 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Athrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Athrips" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Athrips</taxonomicName>
Billberg, 1820), in his 'Group 7 (
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Dichomeris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dichomeris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dichomeris</taxonomicName>
type)' (= 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Dichomeridinae">Dichomeridinae</taxonomicName>
), 
<bibRefCitation pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Karsholt et al. (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 120) in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Gelechiinae">Gelechiinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="tribe" tribe="Chelariini">Chelariini</taxonomicName>
). We follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Ponomarenko, MG" journalOrPublisher="Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" pagination="135 - 142" title="Functional morphology of the male genitalia in the gelechiid-moth genera Holcophora Stgr., Ananarsia Ams., and Nothris Hbn. (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae: Gelechiini, Dichomeridini)." volume="88" year="2009">Ponomarenko (2009</bibRefCitation>
: 195, English translation), who placed 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Holcophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holcophora" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holcophora</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Gelechiinae">Gelechiinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="tribe" tribe="Gelechiini">Gelechiini</taxonomicName>
), based on specifics of the male genitalia musculature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
